<subSubSection pageId="33" pageNumber="184" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="33.[151,1437,151,285]" pageId="33" pageNumber="184">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,151,177]" pageId="33" pageNumber="184">Remarks</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kokujev" authorityYear="1906" box="[324,543,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Ophion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="184" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pravinervis">
<emphasis box="[324,543,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="184">Ophion pravinervis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is previously only known from the now lost 
<typeStatus box="[1053,1101,151,177]" pageId="33" pageNumber="184">type</typeStatus>
material collected in 
<collectingCountry box="[1347,1437,151,177]" name="Georgia" pageId="33" pageNumber="184">Georgia</collectingCountry>
(Kokujev 1906). Proposed as a senior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Ceballos, 1938" authorityName="Ceballos" authorityYear="1938" box="[718,1060,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Ophion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="184" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cortesi">
<emphasis box="[718,885,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="184">Ophion cortesi</emphasis>
Ceballos, 
<quantity box="[1004,1060,187,213]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.92252" pageId="33" pageNumber="184" unit="in" value="1938.0">1938</quantity>
</taxonomicName>
in Rey del Castillo and Izquierdo Moya, based on communication with Pier-Luigi Scaramozzino (1990). This is clearly erroneous as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ceballos" authorityYear="1938" box="[1277,1389,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Ophion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="184" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cortesi">
<emphasis box="[1277,1389,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="184">O. cortesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a valid species of different constitution.
</paragraph>
